50|$|The {{predictions}} {{of the effects of}} <b>a</b> major countervalue <b>nuclear</b> exchange include millions of city dweller deaths within a short period of time. Some 1980s predictions had gone further and argued that <b>a</b> full-scale <b>nuclear</b> <b>war</b> could eventually bring about the extinction of the human race. Such predictions, sometimes but not always based on total <b>war</b> with <b>nuclear</b> arsenals at Cold War highs, received contemporary criticism. A number of Cold War publications advocated preparations that could purportedly enable a large proportion of civilians to survive even <b>a</b> total <b>nuclear</b> <b>war.</b> Among the most famous of these is <b>Nuclear</b> <b>War</b> Survival Skills.|$|R
