5000|$|Some Cold War strategists such as Henry Kissinger {{argued that}} <b>a</b> limited <b>nuclear</b> <b>war</b> could be {{possible}} between two heavily armed superpowers (such as the United States and the Soviet Union). Some predict, however, that a limited war could potentially [...] "escalate" [...] into <b>a</b> full-scale <b>nuclear</b> <b>war.</b> Others have called limited <b>nuclear</b> <b>war</b> [...] "global <b>nuclear</b> holocaust in slow motion", arguing that—once such a war took place—others would {{be sure to}} follow {{over a period of}} decades, effectively rendering the planet uninhabitable {{in the same way that}} <b>a</b> [...] "full-scale <b>nuclear</b> war" [...] between superpowers would, only taking a much longer (and arguably more agonizing) path to the same result.|$|R
